how tocheck if a specific port is open on remote host

check in three ways
--------------------
telnet
netcat 
nmap

if three commands not avaliable in your remote host. just install the commannds
yum install telnet -y
yum install nc -y
yum install nmap -y


how to check ports
-------------------
telnet
------
telnet <hostname/ip address> port number
telnet google.com 443


netcat
------
nc -zv <hostname/ip address> port number
nc -zv google.com 80


nmap
----
nmap -p <port number> <hostname/ip address>
nmap -p 80 google.com


